        <link rel="schema.DC" href="https://purl.org/DC/elements/1.0/" /><meta name="citation_journal_title" content="RadioGraphics" /><meta name="dc.Title" content="Background Parenchymal Enhancement at Breast MR Imaging: Normal Patterns, Diagnostic Challenges, and Potential for False-Positive and False-Negative Interpretation" /><meta name="dc.Creator" content="Catherine S.  Giess" /><meta name="dc.Creator" content="Eren D.  Yeh" /><meta name="dc.Creator" content="Sughra  Raza" /><meta name="dc.Creator" content="Robyn L.  Birdwell" /><meta name="dc.Description" content="This article reviews the anatomic and physiologic influences on BPE, the typical and atypical patterns of BPE, and the potential of BPE to confound accurate interpretation of MR images." /><meta name="Description" content="This article reviews the anatomic and physiologic influences on BPE, the typical and atypical patterns of BPE, and the potential of BPE to confound accurate interpretation of MR images." /><meta name="dc.Description" content="At magnetic resonance (MR) imaging, both normal and abnormal breast tissue enhances after contrast material administration. The morphology and temporal degree of enhancement of pathologic breast ti..." /><meta name="Description" content="At magnetic resonance (MR) imaging, both normal and abnormal breast tissue enhances after contrast material administration. The morphology and temporal degree of enhancement of pathologic breast ti..." /><meta name="dc.Publisher" content="Radiological Society of North America" /><meta name="dc.Date" scheme="WTN8601" content="2014-01-01" /><meta name="dc.Type" content="research-article" /><meta name="dc.Format" content="text/HTML" /><meta name="dc.Identifier" scheme="manuscript" content="135034" /><meta name="dc.Identifier" scheme="doi" content="10.1148/rg.341135034" /><meta name="dc.Source" content="https://doi.org/10.1148/rg.341135034" /><meta name="dc.Language" content="EN" /><meta name="dc.Coverage" content="world" /><met